===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|еҸҖ|еҝғ|t1=|t2=heart|c1=p|c2=s|ls=ic|ls2=psc}}. Originally also written {{zh-l|*еҸҖ}}.

===Etymology===
Related to {{och-l|е”Ҝ|id=1|to be}}. Its usual meaning "kind, compliant" could be semantically extended from "should be" > "to consider / treat as it should / ought to be, as expected" as copulas tend to expand into full verb ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

For pronunciation 2, compare the development of the pronunciation of {{zh-l|з•Ұ}} from {{ltc-l|з•Ұ}}, which historically differed with {{ltc-l|жғ }} only in tone, and is homophonous with {{zh-l|жғ |tr=-}} ({{IPAfont|/Й•iвҒөвҒө/}}) in the modern Xi'an dialect ({{zh-ref|Xi, 2017}}).

